# Get Started – Dyslexia Detection System

This guide explains how to set up and run the project locally after cloning the repository.

---

# Important: Virtual Environment (venv)

The `venv/` folder is **NOT included in Git** (it is ignored using `.gitignore`).
This means:

* There will be ✅ NO issues when someone clones the project
* Each developer creates their own virtual environment locally
* Dependencies are installed using `requirements.txt`

👉 Never commit the `venv/` folder.

---

#  1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <project-folder>
```

---

#  2. Create Virtual Environment

Create a fresh virtual environment:

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Activate it:

### Windows (PowerShell)

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

### Mac/Linux

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
```

You should now see `(venv)` in your terminal.

---

#  3. Install Dependencies

If `requirements.txt` exists:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

If not, install manually:

```bash
pip install fastapi uvicorn scikit-learn pandas numpy joblib python-multipart
add all dependencies which are needed and not mentioned here
```

---

#  4. Train the ML Model (Only First Time)

If the model file does NOT exist:

```
models/gb_eye_pipeline.pkl
```

Run:

```bash
python src/train_model.py
```

This will generate:

* `models/gb_eye_pipeline.pkl`
* `data/synthetic_eye_dyslexia_dataset.csv`

If the model already exists → Skip this step.

---

#  5. Start the FastAPI Server

From the project root directory:

```bash
uvicorn src.server:app --reload
```

If your `server.py` is not inside `src/`, adjust accordingly:

```bash
uvicorn server:app --reload
```

---

#  6. Open in Browser

Once running, you will see:

```
Uvicorn running on http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

Open your browser and visit:

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

---

# 📚 7. API Documentation

FastAPI automatically generates interactive documentation.

Open:

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
```

---

# 🛠️ Common Issues & Fixes

### ❌ ModuleNotFoundError

Make sure you are running commands from the project root directory.

### ❌ Model File Not Found

Run:

```bash
python src/train_model.py
```

### ❌ Port Already in Use

Run on another port:

```bash
uvicorn src.server:app --reload --port 8001
```

---

#  Clean Project Structure (Recommended)

Your repository should contain:

```
src/
models/
data/
requirements.txt
.gitignore
GET_STARTED.md
```

It should NOT contain:

```
venv/
__pycache__/
.idea/
```

