# 👨‍💻 Contribution Workflow

If you are contributing to this project:

1. Go to the repository Issues section.
2. Pick an issue and **assign it to yourself**.
3. Create a separate branch for that issue.

Example:

```bash
git checkout -b feature/issue-name
```

or

```bash
git checkout -b IGL-123-short-description
```

4. Make your changes.
5. Commit with a proper message:

```bash
git commit -m "IGL-123: Short meaningful description"
```

6. Push your branch:

```bash
git push origin <branch-name>
```

7. Create a Pull Request (PR) to the main branch.

⚠️ Do NOT push directly to `master`.
Always work on your own branch.

